<img class="thumbnail aligncenter wp-image-758 size-full" src="https://www.mautic.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/template_email.png" alt="Template email marketing automation list opt-in" width="303" height="287" />

&nbsp;

<img class="thumbnail aligncenter wp-image-755 size-full" src="https://www.mautic.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/opt-in_email.png" alt="Opt-in eamil for marketing automation" width="783" height="512" />

<strong>4. Now create a Campaign form to be used to sign your users up.</strong> This is the very first step in the process. Creating this form as a campaign form means you’ll be able to select it as a source when you build your campaign (next step). You can collect whatever details you wish (remember to keep it simple) and be sure you include their email address as one of your fields.

